README:
Please cite the following reference if you use these data:

Gilbert, S.J., & Fung, H. (2018). Decoding intentions of self and others. NeuroImage. doi: 10.1016/j.neuroimage.2017.12.090.

NB there is no anatomical scan for sub-01

Note that the trial type column in the functional event files corresponds to the trial types shown in Table 1 of the NeuroImage paper.

The event type column specifies the following six events:

1. Beginning of trial (i.e. start of initial thinking time)
2. Player A's response options are presented
3. Player A's response is made and Player B's response options are presented
4. Player B's response is made
5. Feedback is presented
6. End of trial; screen is cleared
